{"title_page": "Marquise Blair", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date = September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{short description|American football player}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Marquise Blair \n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| current_team        = Seattle Seahawks\n| number              = 27\n| position            = [[Safety (gridiron football position)|Safety]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1997|07|18}}\n| birth_place         = [[Wooster, Ohio]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 1\n| weight_lb           = 196\n| high_school         = [[Wooster High School (Ohio)|Wooster HS]]\n| college             = [[Utah Utes football|Utah]]\n| draftyear           = 2019\n| draftround          = 2\n| draftpick           = 47\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Seattle Seahawks]] ({{NFL Year|2019}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          = \n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statweek            = \n| statlabel1          = [[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n| statvalue1          = 32\n| statlabel2          = [[Pass deflected|Pass deflections]]\n| statvalue2          = 1\n| statlabel3          = [[Interceptions]]\n| statvalue3          = 0\n| statlabel4          = [[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n| statvalue4          = 2\n| statlabel5          = [[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n| statvalue5          = 0\n| statlabel6          = [[Touchdown|Defensive touchdowns]]\n| statvalue6          = 0\n| nflnew              = marquiseblair/2562233\n| pfr                 = \n}}\n\n{{short description|American football safety}}\n'''Marquise Blair''' (born July 18, 1997) is an [[American football]] [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] for the [[Seattle Seahawks]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played college football at [[Utah Utes football|Utah]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/sports/utah-utes/2019/04/24/marquise-blair-is-utahs/|title=Marquise Blair is Utah\u2019s top NFL draft prospect, as Chase Hansen\u2019s health makes him a mystery|last=Kragthorpe|first=Kurt|date=April 24, 2019|website=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=September 18, 2019}}</ref>\n==Early years==\nBlair attended [[Wooster High School (Ohio)|Wooster High School]] in [[Wooster, Ohio]] He was a First-team Division II all-state as a senior at Wooster High (Ohio). Also named first-team Division II All-Ohio and Ohio Cardinal Conference Defensive Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite article|title=Marquise Blair bashes his way from Wooster to the Seattle Seahawks|author=Fentress|first=Aaron|date=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nBlair attended  [[Dodge City Community College]] before transferring to [[University of Utah]] after the 2016 season. he was a first-team junior college All-American selection he had over a 100 tackles, 3 [[quarterback sack|sacks]], and 4 [[Interception|interceptions]]. He was an all-conference pick for Dodge City as a freshman.\n\nThe former first-team All-State pick in Ohio eventually worked his way into the starting lineup with the Utes in 2017, starting 6 of 9 games and making over 48 tackles, three for loss, and two pass breakups. before suffering a season-ending injury against UCLA. As a senior, He started in all 14 games with 12 starts in 2018, garnering second-team All-Pac-12 honors along with 17 of his teammates. He finished the year with 59 stops, two for loss, two interceptions, two pass breakups, and a forced fumble.\n\n==Professional career==\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 1\u00bc\n|       weight = 195\n|         dash = 4.48\n|    ten split =\n| twenty split =\n|      shuttle =\n|   cone drill =\n|     vertical = 35.0\n|     broad ft = 10\n|     broad in = 5\n|        bench =\n|     arm span = 30\u00be\n|    hand span = 8\u00bc\n|    wonderlic =\n|         note = All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{cite web|title=Marquise Blair Combine Profile|url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/marquise-blair?id=3219424c-4151-4764-5880-800d375e768a|website=NFL.com|accessdate=November 9, 2019}}</ref> \n}}\n\n===2019===\nBlair was drafted by the [[Seattle Seahawks]] in the second round, 47th overall, of the [[2019 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seahawks.com/news/seahawks-select-utah-safety-marquise-blair-in-second-round-of-2019-nfl-draft|title=Seahawks Select Utah Safety Marquise Blair In Second Round Of 2019 NFL Draft|author=Boyle|first=John|date=April 26, 2019|website=[[Seattle Seahawks]]|url-status=live|access-date=September 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://utahutes.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=7245 Utah Utes bio]\n\n{{Seahawks2019DraftPicks}}\n{{Seattle Seahawks roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blair, Marquise}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Wooster, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Ohio]]\n[[Category:American football safeties]]\n[[Category:Dodge City Conquistadors football players]]\n[[Category:Utah Utes football players]]\n[[Category:Seattle Seahawks players]]\n\n\n{{Defensiveback-1990s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date = September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{short description|American football player}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Marquise Blair \n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| current_team        = Seattle Seahawks\n| number              = 27\n| position            = [[Safety (gridiron football position)|Safety]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1997|07|18}}\n| birth_place         = [[Wooster, Ohio]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 1\n| weight_lb           = 196\n| high_school         = [[Wooster High School (Ohio)|Wooster HS]]\n| college             = [[Utah Utes football|Utah]]\n| draftyear           = 2019\n| draftround          = 2\n| draftpick           = 47\n| pastteams           = \n* [[Seattle Seahawks]] ({{NFL Year|2019}}\u2013present)\n| status              = Active\n| highlights          = \n| statleague          = NFL\n| statseason          = 2019\n| statweek            = \n| statlabel1          = [[Tackle (football move)|Total tackles]]\n| statvalue1          = 32\n| statlabel2          = [[Pass deflected|Pass deflections]]\n| statvalue2          = 1\n| statlabel3          = [[Interceptions]]\n| statvalue3          = 0\n| statlabel4          = [[Fumble|Forced fumbles]]\n| statvalue4          = 2\n| statlabel5          = [[Fumble|Fumble recoveries]]\n| statvalue5          = 0\n| statlabel6          = [[Touchdown|Defensive touchdowns]]\n| statvalue6          = 0\n| nflnew              = marquiseblair/2562233\n| pfr                 = \n}}\n\n{{short description|American football safety}}\n'''Marquise Blair''' (born July 18, 1997) is an [[American football]] [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] for the [[Seattle Seahawks]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played college football at [[Utah Utes football|Utah]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/sports/utah-utes/2019/04/24/marquise-blair-is-utahs/|title=Marquise Blair is Utah\u2019s top NFL draft prospect, as Chase Hansen\u2019s health makes him a mystery|last=Kragthorpe|first=Kurt|date=April 24, 2019|website=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=September 18, 2019}}</ref>\n==Early years==\nBlair attended [[Wooster High School]] in [[Wooster, Ohio]] He was a First-team Division II all-state as a senior at Wooster High (Ohio). Also named first-team Division II All-Ohio and Ohio Cardinal Conference Defensive Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite article|title=Marquise Blair bashes his way from Wooster to the Seattle Seahawks|author=Fentress|first=Aaron|date=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nBlair attended  [[Dodge City Community College]] before transferring to [[University of Utah]] after the 2016 season. he was a first-team junior college All-American selection he had over a 100 tackles, 3 [[quarterback sack|sacks]], and 4 [[Interception|interceptions]]. He was an all-conference pick for Dodge City as a freshman.\n\nThe former first-team All-State pick in Ohio eventually worked his way into the starting lineup with the Utes in 2017, starting 6 of 9 games and making over 48 tackles, three for loss, and two pass breakups. before suffering a season-ending injury against UCLA. As a senior, He started in all 14 games with 12 starts in 2018, garnering second-team All-Pac-12 honors along with 17 of his teammates. He finished the year with 59 stops, two for loss, two interceptions, two pass breakups, and a forced fumble.\n\n==Professional career==\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 1\u00bc\n|       weight = 195\n|         dash = 4.48\n|    ten split =\n| twenty split =\n|      shuttle =\n|   cone drill =\n|     vertical = 35.0\n|     broad ft = 10\n|     broad in = 5\n|        bench =\n|     arm span = 30\u00be\n|    hand span = 8\u00bc\n|    wonderlic =\n|         note = All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{cite web|title=Marquise Blair Combine Profile|url=https://www.nfl.com/prospects/marquise-blair?id=3219424c-4151-4764-5880-800d375e768a|website=NFL.com|accessdate=November 9, 2019}}</ref> \n}}\n\n===2019===\nBlair was drafted by the [[Seattle Seahawks]] in the second round, 47th overall, of the [[2019 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seahawks.com/news/seahawks-select-utah-safety-marquise-blair-in-second-round-of-2019-nfl-draft|title=Seahawks Select Utah Safety Marquise Blair In Second Round Of 2019 NFL Draft|author=Boyle|first=John|date=April 26, 2019|website=[[Seattle Seahawks]]|url-status=live|access-date=September 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://utahutes.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=7245 Utah Utes bio]\n\n{{Seahawks2019DraftPicks}}\n{{Seattle Seahawks roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blair, Marquise}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Wooster, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Ohio]]\n[[Category:American football safeties]]\n[[Category:Dodge City Conquistadors football players]]\n[[Category:Utah Utes football players]]\n[[Category:Seattle Seahawks players]]\n\n\n{{Defensiveback-1990s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Cnwilliams", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Wooster High School\u2192Wooster High School (Ohio)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marquise_Blair"}
